parameters.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationArn
parameters.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the TLS inspection configuration. You must specify the ARN or the name, and you can specify both.

parameters.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationName
parameters.description: The descriptive name of the TLS inspection configuration. You can't change the name of a TLS inspection configuration after you create it. You must specify the ARN or the name, and you can specify both.

nested_items.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationResponse
nested_items.description: The high-level properties of a TLS inspection configuration. This, along with the  TLSInspectionConfiguration, define the TLS inspection configuration. You can retrieve all objects for a TLS inspection configuration by calling  DescribeTLSInspectionConfiguration.

nested_items.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the TLS inspection configuration.

nested_items.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationName
nested_items.description: The descriptive name of the TLS inspection configuration. You can't change the name of a TLS inspection configuration after you create it.

nested_items.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationId
nested_items.description: A unique identifier for the TLS inspection configuration. This ID is returned in the responses to create and list commands. You provide it to operations such as update and delete.

nested_items.name: TLSInspectionConfigurationStatus
nested_items.description: Detailed information about the current status of a  TLSInspectionConfiguration. You can retrieve this for a TLS inspection configuration by calling  DescribeTLSInspectionConfiguration and providing the TLS inspection configuration name and ARN.

nested_items.name: Description
nested_items.description: A description of the TLS inspection configuration.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: The key:value pairs to associate with the resource.

nested_items.name: Key
nested_items.description: The part of the key:value pair that defines a tag. You can use a tag key to describe a category of information, such as 'customer.' Tag keys are case-sensitive.

nested_items.name: Value
nested_items.description: The part of the key:value pair that defines a tag. You can use a tag value to describe a specific value within a category, such as 'companyA' or 'companyB.' Tag values are case-sensitive.

nested_items.name: LastModifiedTime
nested_items.description: The last time that the TLS inspection configuration was changed.

nested_items.name: NumberOfAssociations
nested_items.description: The number of firewall policies that use this TLS inspection configuration.

nested_items.name: EncryptionConfiguration
nested_items.description: A complex type that contains the Amazon Web Services KMS encryption configuration settings for your TLS inspection configuration.

nested_items.name: KeyId
nested_items.description: The ID of the Amazon Web Services Key Management Service (KMS) customer managed key. You can use any of the key identifiers that KMS supports, unless you're using a key that's managed by another account. If you're using a key managed by another account, then specify the key ARN. For more information, see Key ID in the Amazon Web Services KMS Developer Guide.

nested_items.name: Type
nested_items.description: The type of Amazon Web Services KMS key to use for encryption of your Network Firewall resources.

nested_items.name: Certificates
nested_items.description: A list of the certificates associated with the TLS inspection configuration.

nested_items.name: CertificateSerial

nested_items.name: Status
